## 1. `dataset.yaml` тАУ Master Configuration File

The YAML file is the entry point that YOLO reads to locate data and class definitions.

```yaml
# dataset.yaml тАФ MD Trajectory Dataset
path: /home/user/md_trajectory_dataset   # root path
train: images/train                       # relative path to train images
val: images/val                           # relative path to val images
test: images/test                         # optional test set

nc: 2                                     # number of classes
names:
  0: helix                                # alpha-helix structural motif
  1: cluster                              # molecular cluster / aggregate
```

**Key fields:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `path` | Absolute root directory of the dataset |
| `train` / `val` / `test` | Relative paths to image subsets |
| `nc` | Total number of object classes |
| `names` | Class index-to-name mapping |

---

## 2. `train.txt` and `val.txt`

These plain-text files list absolute (or relative) paths to every image in the corresponding split. YOLO iterates over these during training.

```
# train.txt (excerpt)
/home/user/md_trajectory_dataset/images/train/frame_0001.png
/home/user/md_trajectory_dataset/images/train/frame_0007.png
/home/user/md_trajectory_dataset/images/train/frame_0013.png
```

```
# val.txt (excerpt)
/home/user/md_trajectory_dataset/images/val/frame_0601.png
/home/user/md_trajectory_dataset/images/val/frame_0605.png
```

